Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getBlackBoxArea(25.10)                                  getBlackBoxArea(25.10)

Name
       getBlackBoxArea  -  Retrieves  the  standard cell area, macro area, and
       cell utilization value for the specified blackbox

Syntax
       getBlackBoxArea

       [-help]

       -cell <cellName>

       [-stdCellArea]

       [-macroArea]

       [-cellUtil]

       Retrieves the standard cell area,  macro  area,  and  cell  utilization
       value  for  the  specified  blackbox. If only the blackbox cell name is
       specified, the command reports the total blackbox area.

       Note: You can use this command to report the black box area only if you
       had specified the blackbox using the specifyBlackBox command  with  the
       -gateArea parameter.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox cell.

              Data_type: string, required

       -cellUtil
              Reports  the  standard  cell utilization value for the blackbox.
              The standard cell utilization is calculated as follows:

              standard cell area / (blackbox area - total macro area)

              This parameter cannot be used  if  the  blackbox  was  specified
              based on the total area or the gate count.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getBlackBoxArea parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getBlackBoxArea

       -macroArea
              Reports the area of the macros included in  the  blackbox  area.
              This  parameter  cannot  be  used  if the blackbox was specified
              based on the total area or the gate count.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -stdCellArea
              Reports the area of the standard cell included in  the  blackbox
              area.  This  parameter cannot be used if the blackbox was speci-
              fied based on the total area or the gate count.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The following command retrieves the total  blackbox  area  for
                the blackbox bbox_inst1:

                getBlackBoxArea -cell bbox_inst1

              * The  following command retrieves the standard cell area, macro
                area, and cell utilization value for the blackbox bbox_inst2:

                getBlackBoxArea -cell bbox_inst2 -stdCellArea -macroArea -cel-
                lUtil

